ADVANCED & EXTRA FILE MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
# 1. Create a file with content directly
echo "Hello World" > file.txt


Use: Quickly create config files, scripts, notes.

# 2. Append (add text) to a file
echo "New line" >> file.txt
Adds text without replacing old content.

# 3. Create multiple files at once
touch file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt

# 4. Create multiple numbered files
touch log_{1..10}.txt
Creates:

log_1.txt
log_2.txt
...
log_10.txt
Useful for testing.

# 5. Copy only newer files
cp -u source/ dest/
Prevents overwriting newer files.

# 6. Show the top 20 lines
head -20 file.txt

# 7. Show last 20 lines
tail -20 file.txt

# 8. Monitor a file in real-time (LIVE LOGS)
tail -f /var/log/messages

# 9. Count lines, words, characters
wc file.txt

Or individually:

wc -l file.txt   # lines
wc -w file.txt   # words
wc -c file.txt   # characters

# 10. Compare two files
diff file1.txt file2.txt
Shows differences â€” useful for config changes.

# 11. Compress a folder
tar -czvf backup.tar.gz foldername/

# 12. Extract a tar file
tar -xzvf backup.tar.gz

# 13. Delete files older than 7 days
find /tmp -type f -mtime +7 -delete


Real world: clean old logs.

# 14. Find and move files
find . -name "*.log" -exec mv {} logs/ \;


Moves all .log files to logs folder.

# 15. Copy file permissions from one file to another
chmod --reference=config1.yaml config2.yaml
